# Dogfooding artifacts
# The dogfood bundle at the repo root (.agency/skills/superagents/ and
# .claude/skills/superagents-workflow/) IS committed so it survives
# devcontainer rebuilds and exercises the upgrade flow against a real
# committed artifact, matching how every downstream consumer treats
# their bundle. All other root-level .claude/ and .agency/ content
# remains local-only (e.g. .claude/settings.local.json, codex
# worktrees, etc.).
# Patterns are anchored with leading `/` so subtree fixtures like
# examples/generated-skills/*/.{claude,agency}/ are unaffected.
# `**` recursive un-ignore is required to override the global `*.log`
# rule on .agency/skills/superagents/upstream-feedback.log.
/.claude/*
!/.claude/skills/
/.claude/skills/*
!/.claude/skills/superagents-workflow/
!/.claude/skills/superagents-workflow/**
/.agency/*
!/.agency/skills/
/.agency/skills/*
!/.agency/skills/superagents/
!/.agency/skills/superagents/**
# Test fixtures under examples/generated-skills/ have their own
# .claude/ subtrees that should remain ignored (only the .agency/
# metadata bundles are committed for those, not the generated SKILL.md
# files). Anchored above re-included only the root dogfood bundle, so
# we now re-ignore non-root .claude/ subtrees explicitly.
examples/**/.claude/
.codex/
.superagents-dogfood/

# Generated integration files — run scripts/convert.sh to regenerate locally
# The scripts/ and integrations/*/README.md files ARE committed; only generated
# agent/skill files are excluded.
integrations/antigravity/agency-*/
integrations/gemini-cli/skills/
integrations/gemini-cli/gemini-extension.json
integrations/opencode/agents/
integrations/cursor/rules/
integrations/aider/CONVENTIONS.md
integrations/windsurf/.windsurfrules
integrations/openclaw/*
integrations/qwen/agents/
integrations/kimi/*/
!integrations/openclaw/README.md
!integrations/kimi/README.md
